      "The story begins at Mehrgarh, in what is now Balochistan, Pakistan — one of the earliest known farming communities in South Asia, dating to roughly 7000 BCE. Here, archaeologists have unearthed terracotta figurines, many of them female, suggesting an early reverence for the feminine principle — the Mother Goddess — that would persist for millennia and eventually flower into the great Śākta traditions of Devī worship.",
